I think this is one of the places where your ideas about invariants, translation, and compression can be unified into a coherent framework. I’d avoid claiming that “semantic volume” is an objectively measurable quantity today. Instead, I’d define it as an engineering abstraction that Pantheon uses to organize reasoning.

